children.text: The shower walls have been waterproofed in accordance with the Building Code of Australia (BCA) and relevant Australian Standard AS 3740 to prevent water leaks into the structure that could cause damage, however the elevations I have been provided for this area shows a shower rail, which will penetrate the waterproofed shower walls when installed.
Part 3.8.1.2 of the Building Code of Australia (NCC/BCA) - Wet Areas, states that;
‘Building elements in wet areas within a building must-
be waterproof or water resistant in accordance with Table 3.8.1.1; and
Table 3.8.1.1 in the Building Code of Australia (BCA) shows that the penetrations in a shower area must be completely waterproofed;

The builder must install these fixings first, then waterproof and tile around them as required by the NCC’s Building Code of Australia and Australian Standard AS 3740, otherwise these future fixings will penetrate the waterproofing and possibly cause damage.
